Feature Enhancement: Generate Report – Data Persistence, Intelligent Versioning & Pre-Validation Summary

---------------------------------------------------------------------

1. Project Keys – DB Persistence + Refresh

Requirements:
- Fetch project keys from iTrack (Jira) only once
- Persist in DB (e.g., project_keys table)

Behavior:
- On page load:
  - Load from DB (NOT from API)
- Provide button:
  - "Refresh Projects"
    - Re-fetch from iTrack
    - Update DB

UI Enhancements:
- Project Key Dropdown:
  - Add search capability (typeahead)
  - Default selected value: SPTOC1

---------------------------------------------------------------------

2. Release Versions – Persist + Smart UI Filtering

Requirements:
- Fetch all release versions once per project
- Persist in DB (e.g., release_versions table)

Behavior:
- Do NOT reload every time
- Reload only when explicitly triggered

UI Enhancement:
- While displaying dropdown:
  - Show prioritized list:
    - Current Year → Current Month → Current Date onward
    - Highlight current month releases

Important:
- DB must store ALL historical releases

---------------------------------------------------------------------

3. Fix Version Selection Logic (CRITICAL CHANGE)

Rule:
- User selects ONLY Current Fix Version
- DO NOT allow selecting Previous Fix Version manually at global level

---------------------------------------------------------------------

4. Intelligent Previous Version Detection (Per Component)

Problem:
Different components may not exist in same previous release

Solution:

Step 1:
- Identify current branch:
  release/{current_fix_version}

Step 2:
- Dynamically find previous valid branch from GitHub:
  - Iterate backwards:
    26.4.3 → 26.4.2 → 26.4.1 → 26.3.x → 26.2.x ...
  - Check branch existence via GitHub API
  - Select latest available previous branch

Important:
- This logic is component-specific
- DO NOT depend on iTrack for previous versions

---------------------------------------------------------------------

5. Pre-Validation Summary Screen (NEW FEATURE)

Before generating report, show a Summary View

For each Component:
- Component Name
- Scrum Team(s) (multiple possible)
- Current Branch (e.g., release/26.4.3)
- Identified Previous Branch (auto-detected)
- List of Commits:
  - Valid commits only
  - Story IDs
- Unique Stories Count

---------------------------------------------------------------------

6. Component-Level Overrides (User Control)

Provide:
- Dropdown per component:
  - Current Version (default auto-selected)
  - Previous Version (auto-detected but editable)

Allow:
- User override per component before report generation

---------------------------------------------------------------------

7. GitHub Comparison Scope

For each component:
- Compare:
  previous_branch → current_branch

Display in summary:
- Branch comparison range
- Stories involved
- Scrum teams involved

---------------------------------------------------------------------

8. Component Exclusion (Pre-Report)

Problem:
Some components:
- DB Scripts
- NA / No Code
- Test-only

Solution:
- Provide checkbox/toggle:
  - Exclude component from report

Behavior:
- Excluded components:
  - Not processed in report
  - Stored in configuration

---------------------------------------------------------------------

9. Generate Report Execution (Async Processing)

Current Issue:
- UI blocks during processing

Required:
- Run report generation in background thread

Implementation Options:
- Spring Boot:
  - @Async
  - Or Queue-based (Kafka / ExecutorService)

Behavior:
- User can navigate other tabs
- Process continues in background
- On returning:
  - Show latest status/result

---------------------------------------------------------------------

10. Final Report Generation Flow

Steps:

1. User selects:
   - Project Key
   - Current Fix Version

2. System:
   - Loads components from iTrack
   - Identifies previous branch per component
   - Fetches commit data

3. Show Summary Screen

4. User:
   - Reviews data
   - Overrides if needed
   - Excludes components if needed

5. User clicks:
   Generate Report

6. System:
   - Runs async comparison
   - Produces final report (existing logic retained)

---------------------------------------------------------------------

11. Performance Optimization (MANDATORY)

- Cache:
  - Project keys
  - Release versions
- Avoid repeated API calls
- Use DB as primary source

---------------------------------------------------------------------

